I'm looking for feedback, sorry again for such a huge PR. (First, let's see if this passes CI :crossed_fingers:).

title: Drastically improve grammar error messages
body:
Before it would always fail on the highest level possible:
```
16:10:29 - CRITICAL - app:72 - Error reading schema: Failed to parse the schema. Details below:
  @bound_implicitly( characters: vertices, vertices_data )
  ^
  Expected "}" (at char 2660), (line:105, col:1) 

```

Now as low as possible:
```
16:09:44 - CRITICAL - app:72 - Error reading schema: Failed to parse the schema. Details below:
      @explicit_reference( UnaryRelation.kind_ref, strings ä)
                                                           ^
  Expected ")" (at char 3321), (line:121, col:58) 
```

This is done by:
- Using `-` after an expression is *fully commited*, i.e., nothing else could match anymore
- Replacing `^` (longest match) by `|` (first match) where possible

title: Pythonification
body:
The goal is to be able to run `pylint` with a good score in CI. Since this is quite a boring PR, I'll try to make the description a bit less boring.

On the top of my head, this makes the following code smells go away:
- :construction: Access to (some) protected members
- :construction_worker_man: Redefining built-in types
- :writing_hand: Non idiomatic namings
- :nut_and_bolt: Classes with only one public method
- :recycle: Cyclic imports

Bonus: Remove C/C++ semicolons :laughing:
